		'resource_type' : NULL,
		'title' : 'AHIMA, MGMA release letters to HHS on ICD-10 delay',
		'published' : '2012-03-20 10:49:25',
		'status' : 1,
		'summary' : '',
		'body' : 'The American Health Information Management Association (AHIMA) has urged CMS not to delay ICD-10-CM/PCS implementation in its February 23 <a href=\"http://www.ahima.org/downloads/pdfs/advocacy/AHIMA%20Letter%20to%20Secretary%20Sebelius.pdf\">letter to HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius</a>. Meanwhile, the Medical Group Management Association (MGMA) wants HHS to “consider modifying the implementation process to focus on conducting the due diligence necessary for a potential change of this magnitude.”\r\n\r\nHealthcare organizations have already invested a considerable amount of time and resources to preparing for ICD-10-CM/PCS implementation, according to AHIMA’s letter. Because of this investment, AHIMA states its members are critical of HHS’ plan to possibly delay implementation.\r\n\r\nAHIMA calls the updated classification system “essential” for improving healthcare in the United States and fears that those trying to stop ICD-10-CM/PCS implementation don’t understand the classification systems and how they are used.\r\n\r\nDiscussions of a possible delay send the wrong message to healthcare providers, AHIMA says, and it urges HHS to move forward with the October 1, 2013 implementation date.\r\n\r\nMGMA, however, believes HHS needs to create a revised implementation plans before moving forward with ICD-10-CM/PCS. In <a href=\"http://www.mgma.com/WorkArea/mgma_downloadasset.aspx?id=1370049\">its March 1 letter</a>, MGMA outlined seven steps it believes HHS must complete before implementing ICD-10-CM/PCS, including:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Complete a comprehensive cost benefit analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Pilot test ICD-10</li>\r\n	<li>Analyze the administrative and financial impact of overlapping initiatives</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate additional code set approaches</li>\r\n	<li>Stagger implementation dates</li>\r\n	<li>Develop appropriate crosswalks</li>\r\n	<li>Require certification</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMGMA also points out that the healthcare industry is currently struggling to implement HIPAA 5010, adding “it is clear that migration to ICD-10 will be even more complex and costly.”',
		'meta_keywords' : '',
		'volume' : NULL,
		'issue' : NULL,
		'article_position' : NULL
