		'legacy_content_id' : 'W2883',
		'content_type' : 'article',
		'publication' : 'justcoding-website',
		'resource_type' : NULL,
		'title' : 'Some ICD-10-CM files for 2013 released',
		'published' : '2012-07-19 17:06:01',
		'status' : 1,
		'summary' : '',
		'body' : '<a href=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/news01.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-2884\" title=\"news01\" src=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/news01-300x193.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"215\" height=\"138\" /></a>The National Center for Health Statistics, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and CMS have posted some updated files for ICD-10-CM for 2013.\r\n\r\nThe following files are available for download from either the <a href=\"http://www.cdc.gov/nchs/icd/icd10cm.htm#10update\">CDC</a> or <a href=\"http://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Coding/ICD10/2013-ICD-10-CM-and-GEMs.html\">CMS</a> websites:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ICD-10-CM PDF Format</li>\r\n	<li>ICD-10-CM XML Format</li>\r\n	<li>ICD-10-CM 2013 Addenda</li>\r\n	<li>ICD-10-CM List of codes and Descriptions</li>\r\n	<li>General Equivalence Mapping Files</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCMS also posted a file for reimbursement mapping on its site. However, the updated 2013 coding guidelines are not yet available, nor is a summary of the changes.',
