		'summary' : '',
		'body' : 'My brain is fried. Keeping up with all of the mandates and changes in healthcare is exhausting. So is learning the new ICD-10 codes. Maybe I’m just tired because it’s Wednesday. What does ICD-10-CM offer in the way of exhaustion and <a href=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/exhausted-face.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3626\" alt=\"exhausted face\" src=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/exhausted-face-263x300.jpg\" width=\"263\" height=\"300\" /></a>fatigue codes?\r\n\r\nIf we are coding for exhaustion, we need to know the cause What a surprise, right?\r\n\r\nYou’ll find codes for exhaustion due to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cold (T69.8)</li>\r\n	<li>Excessive exertion (T73.3)</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure (T73.2)</li>\r\n	<li>Heat (T67.5, note this is an unspecified code)</li>\r\n	<li>Salt depletion (T67.4)</li>\r\n	<li>Water depletion (T67.3)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe also have:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>F43.0, acute stress reaction (also known as battle fatigue, but not to be confused with post-traumatic stress disorder, F43.1)</li>\r\n	<li>F48.8, other specified nonpsychotic mental disorders, including psychogenic syncope (fainting or weakness caused by states of mind, such as anxiety, hysteria, panic, or major depression)</li>\r\n	<li>R54, age-related physical debility (also known as exhaustion because you’re really old)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nI’m thinking F48.8. We have less than one year until ICD-10 implementation and I’m ready to panic. Some of my coworkers are hysterical, while others seem pretty anxious. Maybe the whole office has a case of mass hysteria. Sadly, ICD-10-CM does not include a code for such a diagnosis.\r\n\r\nUnder fatigue, we see our old favorites F48.8 and R43.0. We also find some new friends:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>R53.82, chronic fatigue, unspecified (Beware, this is another unspecified code)</li>\r\n	<li>R53.83, other fatigue, which includes lack of energy, lethargy, and tiredness</li>\r\n	<li>T67.6, heat fatigue, transient</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWell, I feel completely lethargic, lack energy, and am ready for a nap—R53.83 it is.\r\n\r\nI think it’s time for some coffee or maybe a highly caffeinated soft drink.',
