		'body' : 'It’s the gift-giving season and HCPro is giving you free on-demand access to the audio conference, <b>ICD-10-PCS: Coding, Structure and Format,</b> when you sign up for the January 10 live webcast,<a href=\"http://www.hcmarketplace.com/prod-11554/ICD10PCS-Root-Operations-and-Documentation.html\"><strong>ICD-10-PCS: Root</strong></a><a href=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/dont-miss-it.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3608\" alt=\"dont miss it\" src=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/dont-miss-it-300x252.jpg\" width=\"215\" height=\"181\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.hcmarketplace.com/prod-11554/ICD10PCS-Root-Operations-and-Documentation.html\"><strong> Operations and Documentatio</strong></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.hcmarketplace.com/prod-11554/ICD10PCS-Root-Operations-and-Documentation.html\">n</a></strong>.\r\n\r\nExpert speakers <b>Mark N. Dominesey, MBA, RN, CCDS, CDIP, CHTS-CP, </b>and<b> Nena Scott, MSEd, RHIA, CCS, CCS-P, </b>AHIMA-Approved ICD-10-CM/PCS Trainer, build the foundation for ICD-10-PCS coding in <b>ICD-10-PCS: Coding, Structure and Format</b>. Once you master the basics, you\'ll be ready to dive into the nuances of the root operations.\r\n\r\nOn January 10, Mark and Nina will break down the 31 root operations into nine groups of related root operations. They will explain how to choose between root operations with similar definitions and provide insight on what to look for in documentation during the January 10 program. In addition, Mark and Nina will answer your questions live. Don\'t miss it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',
		'meta_keywords' : '',
