		'status' : 1,
		'summary' : '',
		'body' : '<a href=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/dont-miss-it.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3608\" alt=\"dont miss it\" src=\"http://blogs.hcpro.com/icd-10/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/dont-miss-it-300x252.jpg\" width=\"221\" height=\"185\" /></a>You can stop holding your breath. <b>Shelley C. Safian, PhD, MAOM/HSM, CCS-P, CPC-H, CPC-I, CHA</b>, AHIMA-approved ICD-10-CM/PCS trainer, and <b>Tara L. Bell, RN, MSN, CCM,</b> AHIMA-approved ICD-10-CM/PCS trainer, are ready to explain everything you need to know about ICD-10-CM respiratory coding.\r\n\r\nJoin us at 1 p.m. (Eastern) Tuesday, February 11, for the live 90-minute webcast, <a href=\"http://hcmarketplace.com/icd-10-cm-respiratory-coding-22990\"><b>Transition to ICD-10-CM respiratory coding: Anatomy, documentation, and guidelines</b></a><b>.</b>\r\n\r\nTo make sure everyone starts with the proper foundation, Shelley and Tara will review respiratory anatomy. They’ll also review the ICD-10-CM guidelines and explain what information you need to find in the medical record documentation for ICD-10-CM respiratory conditions.\r\n\r\nBy the time the program ends, you’ll know about the changes to asthma and pneumonia terminology and the new tobacco use, abuse, and dependence codes.\r\n\r\nCan’t listen live? No problem. We also offer the program on-demand. If you sign up for the live program, the on-demand version is included, so you can listen again.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hcmarketplace.com/icd-10-cm-respiratory-coding-22990\">Sign up now!</a>',
