		'body' : 'Gerri Walk, senior manager of technical training for HRS in Baltimore, had the absolute best reason for learning to code in ICD-10. During the 2013 AHIMA National Conference in Atlanta, Gerri declared ICD-10 was helping us stave off dementia. She got a huge laugh from the audience.\r\n\r\nShe also a gave a great reason for brushing up on your anatomy and physiology, especially for ICD-10-PCS cardiac procedures. “The vessels of the heart are like roads in Texas,” Gerri said. “Turn a corner and you’re on a different road or in a different vessel.”\r\n\r\nShe was very good at engaging her audience. Don’t believe me? Listen for yourself. She presented on two webinars for HCPro earlier this year, Reduce the Fear of ICD-10-CM Cardiovascular Coding and Reduce the Fear of ICD-10-PCS Cardiovascular Procedures (both available on-demand).\r\n\r\nI was very fortunate to have the opportunity to work with Gerri on a number of projects (including those two webinars), so I was very sad to learn last week that Gerri had passed away. Her dedication, knowledge, and coding humor will be missed.',
