		'status' : 1,
		'summary' : '',
		'body' : 'Great tip from 3M\'s Donna Smith, the Association of Clinical Documentation Improvement Specialists conference general session speaker.\r\n\r\n\"We\'re collecting data for the future. It is a little shortsighted to just ask, which DRG changes affect the bottom line.\"\r\n\r\nYou probably won\'t see much change initially with DRG payments. In fact, most experts predict only a 1-2% shift in DRGs initially. However, that is likely to change the longer we use ICD-10. CMS uses two years\' worth of claims data when calculating payment rates, so once the agency has that data, it could make significant changes to DRG assignments.\r\n\r\nDonna also offered another great reminder: \"We want to make sure we are reporting all of the diagnoses important to the patient for severity of illness.\"\r\n\r\nThe better we can illustrate how sick our patients are and the resources we used to treat them, the better off we\'ll be.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',
